This paper deals with resource allocation in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also discusses power control algorithms, which is a sub-topic of information theory (cs.IT). The proposed algorithm is designed to improve the energy efficiency of the network, which is a system-level concern and falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of Long Term Evolution (LTE), which is a topic related to multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of the proposed algorithm, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
